<p>Southwest Fort Wayne's newer developments, including areas near Covington Road, often feature homes already equipped with higher-efficiency HVAC systems, making solar additions straightforward and cost-effective. The Leo-Cedarville area, with its rural character and larger properties, provides excellent opportunities for larger solar installations and geothermal HVAC systems. Downtown Fort Wayne's urban core presents unique challenges with row houses and limited roof space, making community solar programs and ductless mini-split systems attractive alternatives for energy efficiency improvements.</p>

